<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1631">
There are $n$ books, and Kotivalo and Justiina are going to read them all. For each book, you know the time it takes to read it.<br />
<br />
They both read each book from beginning to end, and they cannot read a book at the same time. What is the minimum total time required?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the number of books.<br />
<br />
The second line has $n$ integers $t_1,t_2,\dots,t_n$: the time required to read each book.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the minimum total time.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le t_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>3<br />
2 8 3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>16</code>    </div>
